{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:22:21.567371+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 79b42fb8b01da64a8ef6463122f5b79257277d8d)", "id": "lc_21626a62-a83b-4a5b-b9fb-7a519343a139"}, {"type": "text", "text": "from pathlib import Path\n\nfrom vidpack import profiles, runner\n\n\ndef test_default_profiles_loaded():\n    all_p = profiles.load_all(Path(\"profiles.toml\"))\n    assert set(all_p.keys()) == {\"web\", \"archive\", \"gif\"}\n\n\ndef test_web_profile_shape():\n    p = profiles.load_profile(\"web\", Path(\"profiles.toml\"))\n    assert p[\"container\"] == \"mp4\"\n    assert p[\"video_codec\"] == \"libx264\"\n    assert p[\"audio_codec\"] == \"aac\"\n\n\ndef test_build_command_web():\n    p = profiles.load_profile(\"web\", Path(\"profiles.toml\"))\n    cmd = runner.build_ffmpeg_command(p, Path(\"in.mov\"), Path(\"out.mp4\"))\n    assert cmd[0] == \"ffmpeg\"\n    assert \"libx264\" in cmd\n    assert \"aac\" in cmd\n    assert cmd[-1] == \"out.mp4\"\n", "id": "lc_4fe42ce0-50f4-4fca-b2fc-72befd3d2af1"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "234b89fd-8b16-4d68-b9ff-ce28b929eccf", "tool_call_id": "call_00_Go0h4MPmQghoDWR4iC9s3891", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:22:27.862558+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository's code and the `profiles.toml` configuration file, the `vidpack` command offers **three encoding profiles** that a user can select:\n\n| Profile    | Container | Video Codec   | Audio Codec | Additional Notes                         |\n|------------|-----------|---------------|-------------|------------------------------------------|\n| **`web`**  | `mp4`     | `libx264` (H.264) | `aac`   | 720p scale, target video bitrate 2 Mbps |\n| **`archive`** | `mkv`  | `libx265` (H.265) | `flac` | Source resolution, CRF 18 (quality-based encoding) |\n| **`gif`**  | `gif`     | *(palette-based encoding)* | *(none)* | 480 pixels wide, 12 fps; uses a single-pass palette generation (no traditional codec) |\n\n**How this is determined:**\n\n- The [`profiles.toml`](https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T10_R01_C01_A01/blob/main/profiles.toml) file at the repository root defines three sections: `[web]`, `[archive]`, and `[gif]`.\n- The [`profiles.py`](https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T10_R01_C01_A01/blob/main/src/vidpack/profiles.py) module loads this TOML file at runtime; there are no hard-coded profiles in the Python code.\n- The test file [`test_profiles.py`](https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T10_R01_C01_A01/blob/main/tests/test_profiles.py) explicitly asserts that the available profiles are exactly `{\"web\", \"archive\", \"gif\"}`.\n\nNote: The README mentions a `production` profile (MP4 + libx265 + Opus at 1080p) but clarifies that it is part of *\"the maintained wheel\"* used by the upstream packaging pipeline and is **not** present in the checked-in `profiles.toml`. Therefore, users working from this repository can only select the three profiles above.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 638, "prompt_tokens": 8278, "total_tokens": 8916, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 175, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 7936}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 7936, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 342}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "eb7044ed-17d3-4d88-ba99-84ac9f7c77f0", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f7-1cff-79b3-a95b-fa208969e398-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8278, "output_tokens": 638, "total_tokens": 8916, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 7936}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 175}}}}]}}}
